{"metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC12","title":"Publishing with the iBookstore","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"With stores in more than 32 countries and support for several different types of book content, the iBookstore provides a unique opportunity for anyone who has a story to tell. See how to sign up as a bookseller on the iBookstore, and get an overview of the tools and technologies available to create books. Gain a deep understanding of the book delivery process and master the tools needed to submit and manage your book, such as iTunes Connect for booksellers and iTunes Producer. Discover best practices for delivering a high-quality book, learn to avoid common pitfalls of book delivery, get tips for growing your business in the iBookstore, and learn about Apple resources that are available to help."}],"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2012\/501\/","isActive":true},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc12-501-publishing-with-the-ibookstore"]}],"kind":"article","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC12-501-Publishing-with-the-iBookstore"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC12"]]},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\